-- South African Lending Improved in Quarter Through June, Business Day Says
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2010-09-29T05:56:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/south-african-lending-improved-in-quarter-through-june-business-day-says.html
New credit granted in South Africa
increased to 67.55 billion rand in the quarter through June from
61.55 billion rand in the prior three months, Business Day said,
citing a report, which will be released by the National Credit
Regulator today.  Mortgage lending accounted for the largest share of loans
provided for the first time in a year, the Johannesburg-based
newspaper said.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
